---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="About VideoGenNews"
  description="Mission, ownership, and editorial standards for VideoGenNews."
  breadcrumbs={[{ name: 'About' }]}
>
  <section class="hero-panel compact">
    <p class="hero-kicker">About</p>
    <h1>About VideoGenNews</h1>
    <p>VideoGenNews is a specialist publication focused on AI video tools, model behavior, workflows, and policy.</p>
  </section>

  <section class="story-shell">
    <h2>Mission</h2>
    <p>Publish clear, source-linked reporting on AI video products and ecosystem changes.</p>
    <p>Our reporting standards and source-label system are documented on the <a href="/methodology/">Methodology</a> page.</p>

    <h2>Ownership and funding</h2>
    <p>VideoGenNews is independently operated by the VideoGenNews Desk.</p>
    <p>Current revenue channels: sponsorships and newsletter placements. Sponsored material is labeled.</p>

    <h2>Editorial standards</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>Every story includes an author and visible publish/update timestamps.</li>
      <li>Material claims are tied to visible sources, with source tiers shown on article pages.</li>
      <li>Corrections are published visibly and timestamped.</li>
      <li>News and analysis are labeled by content type.</li>
      <li>We prioritize official release notes, product docs, and on-record statements for factual claims.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Reporting workflow</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>Each story is desk-owned and has a named reporter or desk byline.</li>
      <li>Primary-source coverage is preferred; secondary context is labeled as context.</li>
      <li>When facts change, we update the story timestamp and append correction notes when needed.</li>
    </ul>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
